  description: "\\emph{Under raging stormclouds, a lone figure stands upon the ancient walls of \\Place{Castle Ravenloft}. Lightning splits the sky, its cold light revealing a tall form wrapped in a billowing cape of shadows. Another flash exposes a face full of power and madness, contorted by a tragedy darker than the night. Far below, a party of adventurers has entered his dread domain. He smiles. Another lightning bold rips through the night, but the figure is gone. Only a howling wind fills the midnight air. domain. \\NPC{Strahd}\'s face forms a twisted smile as his dark plan unfolds. He knew they were coming, and he knows why they came, all according to his plan. He, the master of \\Place{Ravenloft}, will attend to them. The master of \\Place{Castle Ravenloft} is having guests for dinner---and you\'re invited!} Originally published in 1983, this classic adventure for four to eight characters of levels 5 to 7 mixes elements of gothic horror with AD&D fantasy for a unique experience. Updated to 2nd Edition, \\Product{Ravenloft} features a haunted castle, gypsy fortunetellers, a tragic back story, and a \\Monster{vampire} who is as powerful and intelligent as he is frightening---a menace worthy of the braves adventuring party!"
